Roasting the @cauliflower{1%unit}(whole) crown whole allows the exterior to develop a deliciously golden brown crust. Similarly, @chickpeas{1%can} become crispy on the outside and creamy on the inside when oven-roasted. A generous drizzle of dilled yogurt sauce completes this Mediterranean-inspired plate!

Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Strip and discard the leaves from the bottom of the cauliflower, then trim the stem so it sits flat on the #baking sheet{}. Drizzle the cauliflower crown with @olive oil{2%tablespoons}. Season with @salt{}, @pepper{}, and @cumin{1/2%teaspoon}. Roast on a baking sheet for about ~{40%minutes}, until tender and golden brown.

Meanwhile, drain and rinse the chickpeas, then pat them dry with paper towel. Toss in a #small bowl{} with @coriander{1/2%teaspoon}, @olive oil{1%tablespoon}, and a large pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Place on the baking sheet with the cauliflower and roast for ~{15-20%minutes}, until crispy.

Use a #small paring knife{}, remove and discard the peel and white pith of the @orange{1%unit}, cutting carefully around the flesh. Working over a small bowl, hold the peeled orange in one hand and cut between the membranes to remove each orange segment. Squeeze the remaining orange core over another small bowl to collect any juice. Reserve the orange juice and segments separately.

== Dilled Yogurt Sauce ==

Finely chop the @dill{1%bunch}, then combine half the chopped dill, @yogurt{1/2%cup}(Greek), and @cumin{1/2%teaspoon} to the bowl with the orange juice. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Plating ==

When the cauliflower is golden brown, cut into quarters and plate on a bed of roasted chickpeas and orange segments. Drizzle dilled yogurt over top and garnish with remaining dill and @pepitas{1%ounce}. Enjoy!